c WMC: x1 <-> x2 forces an equivalence; after the merge the only clauses that
c mention them ((1,-2),(-1,2)) become satisfied and the class goes FREE.
c This exercises the "merged-then-free" path: applyEquivalences picks a survivor
c (root fallback, no alive member), folds x1's weight into it, and
c applyIsolatedVars must then fold w(s)+w(~s) over the folded weights.
c proj = {1,2}.  Valid projected assignments under x1==x2: (T,T) and (F,F).
c Exact answer = w1+ * w2+  +  w1- * w2-
c              = 3/10*4/10 + 7/10*6/10 = 12/100 + 42/100 = 54/100 = 0.54
c t wmc
p cnf 2 2
c p weight 1 3/10 0
c p weight -1 7/10 0
c p weight 2 4/10 0
c p weight -2 6/10 0
1 -2 0
-1 2 0
